Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setIlmType(25.10)                                            setIlmType(25.10)

Name
       setIlmType - Controls the behavior of commands in the presence of ILMs

Syntax
        setIlmType

       [-help]

       [-model {timing | si}]

       Controls the behavior of commands in the presence of ILMs.

       ILM models can be an SI model or a non-SI model. In the flow, sometimes
       an  explicit flattenIlm needs to be performed to perform the underlying
       operation. Based on the nature of operation, an appropriate model could
       be invoked/switched with the above command.

       Use the getIlmType command to display  the  current  settings  for  the
       setIlmType command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setIlmType parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setIlmType.

       -model {timing | si}
              Specifies the ILM model that is to be  used  by  the  flattenIlm
              command.  All  the timing-related commands require data to be in
              the  flattened  state  (physical  command  require   unflattened
              state).

              Design  commands  such as optDesign and timeDesign automatically
              set this parameter before flattening ILMs. However, the CTE com-
              mands and some clock commands, which can be run in the flattened
              mode require manual settings.

              * Use the si model for flattening the SI ILM model.

              * Use the timing model for flattening the non-SI related  timing
                commands.

              Note:  In  case  of  non-merged models, use the cts model before
              running flattenIlm followed by the command which directly  deals
              with the clocks.

              Default: timing

Examples
              * The  following  command  is  used  to report clock tree in the
                presence of ILMs:

                flattenIlm

                reportClockTree

                unflattenIlm

                The unflattenIlm command resets -model to  its  default  value
                timing since the next command is not a clock command.

              * The  following  command can be used to get timing reports con-
                taining the SI push-out delays on nets using the  -setIlmType-
                model command:

                setIlmType -model si

                # Flattens to SI model

                flattenIlm

                # Turns on SI aware delay calculation

                setDelayCalMode -SIAware true

                # Adds incremental delay column (for SI push-out delays)

                #  in timing output:

                set_global_report_timing_format {instance arc cell fanout load
                slew delay incr_delay arrival}

                # Minimizes the width of the report such that it easily

                # fits into the screen without wrapping

                set_table_style -name report_timing -no_frame -indent 0

                report_timing

       Note:  You  can  also invoke the Global Timing Debugger (Timing - Debug
       Timing - Generate)

Related Information
              * flattenIlm

              * getIlmType

              * optDesign

              * timeDesign

              * Top-level Timing Closure Methodologies chapter of Innovus User
                Guide.

